			<div class = "uc col-sm-8 project-info">
				<div class = "project-download-play">
					<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mmarvick.uc_lite">
						<img 
							src="<%= image_path("play_store_download.png")%>"
							alt="Download Urgent Call on Google Play"
						>
					</a>
				</div>
				<div class = "project-descrip">
					<h3>
						Urgent Call lets users silence their phone, eliminate distraction, and still be reached when needed most.
					</h3>
					<p>
						Urgent Call allows people to put their phone into silent mode, but still receive alerts if they receive 3 calls from the same person in less than 15 minutes, or get a text message with the phrase "Urgent!" embedded in it. Alert triggers are customizable, can be filtered by contact, and users can add new alert rules to tailor the alerts to different situations.
					</p>
					<p>
						Primary learnings from this project include:
					</p>
					<ul>

						<li>Careful evaluation of tradeoffs between form and function to keep the user interface clean and simple, yet filled with customization to satisfy most users</li>
						<li>Storing data in a flexible structure that makes upgrades easier</li>
						<li>Separating the presentation of the data and user interface from the manipulation of the data</li>
						<li>Creating custom Views to simplify code and reduce repitition</li>
						<li>Strategic use of abstraction to prevent duplicating code between the different alert types (call and text alerts)</li>
						<li>Frequent code refactorization and documentaton to keep the codebase managable and maintainable</li>	
						<li>Advertising, marketing, and responding to user feedback to encourage more use of the app</li>
					</ul>

				</div>

